./src/FlawVerifier.sol:75:        uint256 strategyMarkedValue = IStrategyDAICurve(TARGET).balanceOf();
./src/FlawVerifier.sol:79:                "Controller returned no live DAI vault, so the public deposit trigger vault.earn() was unreachable. "
./src/FlawVerifier.sol:80:                "withdrawAll() is controller-only, and the captured fork therefore exposes no public path into the zero-min Curve calls.";
./src/FlawVerifier.sol:100:            "The captured logs already showed the strategy started empty, so the exit paths withdraw(uint) and withdrawAll() had no pre-existing strategy inventory to unwind before a prior earn(), and withdrawAll() remains controller-only. "
./src/FlawVerifier.sol:101:            "Exploit causality is unchanged: public vault.earn() is still the reachable path into strategy.deposit() -> add_liquidity([_y,0,0,0], 0).";
./src/FlawVerifier.sol:105:                "The live DAI vault held no idle DAI at this fork block, so the public deposit trigger vault.earn() had nothing to forward into strategy.deposit() -> add_liquidity([_y,0,0,0], 0). "
./src/FlawVerifier.sol:110:                "The verifier therefore kept the exploit aligned to vault.earn() -> strategy.deposit() -> add_liquidity([_y,0,0,0], 0) and did not claim the controller-only withdrawAll() path.";
./src/FlawVerifier.sol:164:        // public deposit path vault.earn() -> strategy.deposit() -> add_liquidity([_y,0,0,0], 0).
./src/FlawVerifier.sol:239:                    "flashswap(DAI) -> vault.earn() -> strategy.deposit() -> add_liquidity([_y,0,0,0], 0)",
./src/FlawVerifier.sol:240:                    "Borrowed DAI from a pre-existing UniswapV2/Sushi-like pair, converted it into yDAI, skewed the Curve y-pool with exchange(0,1,...,0), let the honest public vault.earn() route idle vault DAI through the strategy's zero-min add_liquidity([_y,0,0,0], 0), then back-ran the pool and repaid the flashswap from the extracted DAI spread."
